result.execSummary:
The defendant Hannah Lynn Klingensmith was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: 3 days jail credit, only if revoked.

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.

No consumption or possession of alcohol.
No entry into any bars or taverns, except for purposes of assisting/visiting her grandmother, whom owns a bar.
Expungement aurhorized under 973.015 if probation is completely satisfied.
The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Hannah Lynn Klingensmith in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 3:18 PM. Also called 15CM128. Burns - resolved. State 15CM80 - DRI only count in this case. Court explains what it means to be DRI, Klingensmith undertands and Court dismisses and reads in case. On 15CM128 - plead to both counts as alleged, withhold sentence and place on probation for 18 months with conditions of: court costs on each count, AODA and follow, employment/school, no alcohol or entry into any bars or taverns, 30 hours of community service. Burns and Kligensmith agree. Kligensmith pleads NC to both counts as alleged on 15CM128. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State - follow joint recommendation. Burns - follow joint recommendation - asks if defendant can petition for early release of probation after 1 year, 3 days jail credit only if revoked, requests expungement. State has no objections to the early release from probation but will not agree with it either, believes it is a DOC decision. Court agrees. Klingensmith withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: on each count - withhold sentence and place on probation for 18 months - concurrent to each other, with conditions of: court costs on each count - paid thru probation, AODA and follow, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, no consumption or possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns except for purposes of assiting/visiting her grandmother that owns a bar, 30 hours of community service total, submit DNA sample and expungment information given, credit for 3 days only if revoked, authorize expungement under 973.015 if probation is completely satisfied, right to appeal, adjourned.

Defendant Hannah Lynn Klingensmith in court.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:14 AM. Recalled at 9:22 AM. Burns appears specially today but the defendant has to contact SPD for qualification. Burns has complaint but believes the bail jumping charges is not appropriate for stated reasons. State responds - previous case has not been dismissed yet. Court reviews file. Burns enters NG pleas to all counts, asks for FPT date, asks for signature bond for stated reasons. State - bond - no objections to signature bond. Court refunds bond to poster, sets bond at $500.00 signature bond - no consumption of alcohol, set for FPT on 9/23/15 at 3:00 PM, also set 15CM80 for FPT on same date and time.
